  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "透明錯覺 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-illusion-of-transparency",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / communication / clarity / teams</p>\n    <h1>透明錯覺</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Illusion of Transparency</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">我們常以為自己的意圖、緊張、顧慮或重點已經很明顯，但對別人來說，那些內心註解往往根本沒有被看見。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『我心裡很清楚』和『別人真的收到了』拆開，因為許多溝通失敗都不是沒善意，而是高估了自己有多透明。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>溝通偏誤 / 自我可見性</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>People overestimate how obvious their thoughts and feelings are to others</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>內在清晰度、外顯訊號、對方背景、驗證方式</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能在說明、會議與 code review 裡更主動把腦中沒說出的判準外顯出來</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>內心</span>\n      <span>外顯</span>\n      <span>落差</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>你心裡那段註解，通常不會自己長到別人腦中</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">透明錯覺抓到的是一個常見誤判：我們太容易把自己感受得到的清晰，誤當成別人也看得到。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>內心模型越成熟，越容易低估外顯訊號其實不夠；結果自己以為已經說清楚，對方卻只收到一半。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先承認內在清楚不等於外在清楚</strong>\n        <p>你知道自己在想什麼，不代表別人能從幾句話就補完。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再把判準講出來</strong>\n        <p>特別是你覺得『這不是很 obvious 嗎』的地方，常最該外顯。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後驗證理解</strong>\n        <p>不要只看對方點頭，要看對方能不能用自己的話重建。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一次你以為自己已經說很明白、對方卻完全沒接到的溝通開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">透明錯覺在 mentoring、跨部門協作與高壓討論裡特別常見。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>你在會議上說『這個風險我有點擔心』，心裡其實是覺得極可能翻車；但對別人來說，這只是常規保留意見。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>真正缺的不是更多誠意，而是把強度、脈絡與判準說到足夠可見。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">內在意圖自覺很強</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">外顯訊號卻不夠明確</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">對方收到的版本大幅縮水</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>透明錯覺最值得警惕的地方，是它讓善意溝通也能產生巨大落差。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看可見性落差的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">與其怪對方沒懂，不如先問自己有沒有把真正重要的內心註解送出來。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>強度是否外顯</strong>\n        <p>你覺得『非常擔心』，但語句是否只表達成『有點需要看一下』？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>背景是否共享</strong>\n        <p>你腦中的上下文，對方真的也有嗎？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>語意是否具體</strong>\n        <p>模糊保留語是否讓真正判斷被沖淡了？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>驗證是否存在</strong>\n        <p>你有沒有確認對方收到的其實是同一件事？</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>情境</th>\n            <th>自己以為已傳達的</th>\n            <th>對方可能實際收到的</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>風險提示</td>\n            <td>這很危急</td>\n            <td>只是常規保守意見</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Code review</td>\n            <td>這種寫法很危險</td>\n            <td>作者可能只覺得你偏好不同風格</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>教學說明</td>\n            <td>步驟已講清楚</td>\n            <td>新手只收到片段指令，沒收到判準</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼我們這麼容易高估自己的透明度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為自己的情緒、意圖與上下文一直在腦中發亮，很難想像別人其實看不到那盞燈。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>內在訊號太亮</strong>\n        <p>自己感受到的強度會讓人誤以為外顯也很強。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>共享背景被高估</strong>\n        <p>同團隊、同語境讓人容易以為對方知道得跟自己差不多。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>點頭會製造錯覺</strong>\n        <p>社交上的禮貌反應很容易被誤讀成真正理解。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">透明錯覺不是叫你把一切說爆，而是提醒你腦中的清楚並不會自動外送。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把可見性補回文件、會議與 review</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對工程與跨團隊合作來說，許多『我不是早就講過』的挫折，根本上都和透明錯覺有關。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>風險溝通</strong>\n        <p>如果某個風險真的是 blocker，就要用能讓對方感受到 blocker 的語言，而不是一般保留語。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>文件撰寫</strong>\n        <p>內在已串好的因果如果不展開，讀者只會看到斷裂步驟。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>Mentoring</strong>\n        <p>你以為自己示範過了，對方卻可能只模仿動作，沒學到背後判準。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>當事情很重要時，請把『我真正擔心的是什麼、程度多高、為何如此判斷』說得比平常更明白。</li>\n      <li>驗證理解最有效的方法通常不是問『有沒有問題』，而是請對方重述或實際走一遍。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">透明錯覺不是說別人不會讀空氣，而是說重要事情不能靠讀空氣。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要講得更長就行</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>不是。關鍵是把真正缺失的判準與強度補出來。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>對方沒懂就是沒在聽</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>有時其實是你把內在上下文高估成外顯訊號。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>這只發生在口語溝通</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>文件、註解、PR 描述與簡報都很常中招。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>我覺得明顯的地方，對方真的看得到嗎</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">下面兩個問題很適合放在重要溝通前後。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>如果把我心裡那段沒說出的註解拿掉，現在這段話還夠清楚嗎</strong>\n        <p>這能快速找出透明落差。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>對方若用自己的話重述，會不會重建出同樣判斷</strong>\n        <p>若不會，清楚感很可能只存在你腦中。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 curse of knowledge、communication theory 與 shared context。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 illusion of transparency 為主，再把概念帶回團隊溝通、教學與風險說明。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Illusion of transparency 條目整理了人如何高估自己內在狀態對他人的可見性。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illusion_of_transparency\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Illusion of Transparency</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>近鄰偏誤</strong>\n        <p>Curse of knowledge 可作為對照，看專家如何高估他人起點與理解。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Curse_of_knowledge\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Curse of Knowledge</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>溝通背景</strong>\n        <p>Communication 條目可作為更一般背景，理解訊號與理解之間的落差。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Communication\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Communication</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以找一段你最近說過『我不是早就說了』的溝通，重看它到底有沒有把真正判準說出來。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
